I'm different, just like everybody else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uakbarbelakesh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akbar BelAkesh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/28/01 12:56:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: what stuns do you use?</span><hr size=1> I use entrance for the recast delay and the mana cost.  People seem surprised when I tell them... but they never question my decision once they've seen me use it heh.<br>
<br>
I was trying to think back to why I first started using two stuns... I remember alllll the way back on orc highway.  I was trying to charm the orcs at level 16 or so.. they would break and I thought at the time.. gee wouldn't it be nice to have another stun to give me some more time to mez/charm. <br>
<br>
I've just always used them since them ( since I got the second one ).<br>
<br>
I find it extremely useful with charm.  The lower level stun is easier to channel and a faster cast.  The higher level stun is slower to cast but longer duration.  You can nestle a recharm very nicely while a monster is stunned for 8 seconds.  <br>
<br>
Sometimes if you have 2-3+ mobs on you it can be handy to have a second stun loaded and ready to go.  They can resist, you could have an unexpected add from someplace, any number of things could happen that make the second stun a desirable thing.  <br>
<br>
I look at the stuns as my &quot;armor&quot; so to speak.  Sometimes I wish I had the spell slots for 3 stuns heh.  <br>
<br>
